The cameras detect targets successfully ( hasTargets() is true ), and we’re printing the best tag ID for each camera to SmartDashboard. However, we never receive any estimated robot poses — the update() method always returns Optional.empty() .

Things we’ve tried:

Using identity Transform3d() for the camera position (to rule out transform issues)

Switching strategies from MULTI_TAG_PNP_ON_COPROCESSOR to LOWEST_AMBIGUITY

Confirmed tags are visible in the PhotonVision web UI

Confirmed correct camera names

Confirmed AprilTagFieldLayout is loaded via AprilTagFields.k2024Crescendo.loadAprilTagLayoutField()

At this point, we’re stuck — we can see tags, but no pose is estimated. Has anyone else run into this with PhotonLib 2025.x? Are we missing something critical about how the estimator expects input or field layout?

